results.name: a(n) is the number of elements added at n-th stage in the structure of the finite cellular automaton of A299770.
comment: The word of this cellular automaton is abcd. For more information see A296612.
link: N. J. A. Sloane, Catalog of Toothpick and Cellular Automata Sequences in the OEIS
Index entries for sequences related to cellular automata
Index entries for sequences related to toothpick sequences
example: The finite sequence can be written as an array of four columns as shown below:
The first column gives the number of toothpicks of length 2.
The second column gives the number of D-toothpicks of length sqrt(2).
The third column gives the number of toothpicks of length 1.
The fourth column gives the number of T-toothpicks.
xref: For other hybrid cellular automata, see A289841, A290221, A294021, A294981.
